# Conventions — {{.Project}}

> TypeScript style + naming + structural rules. PRs / agent sessions that
> violate these are rejected by the reviewer.

## Naming

- Files: `kebab-case.ts` for modules; `PascalCase.tsx` for React
  components.
- Types & interfaces: `PascalCase`. Don't prefix with `I` (use
  `User`, not `IUser`).
- Functions & variables: `camelCase`. Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` only
  for true compile-time constants.
- React component file matches its exported component name.

## File structure

- One default export max per file (and only when it's the file's reason
  to exist).
- Named exports for everything else.
- Tests live next to the code: `foo.ts` + `foo.test.ts`.

## Errors

- Throw `Error` subclasses, never plain strings.
- Define domain errors:
  ```ts
  export class NotFoundError extends Error {
    constructor(public readonly id: string) {
      super(`not found: ${id}`);
    }
  }
  ```
- Functions document what they throw in JSDoc (`@throws`).

## Async

- Mark async functions `async` even when only `await`ing one call —
  hoists the return type.
- `Promise.all` for parallel work; never serial `await` in loops when
  the work is independent.
- `@typescript-eslint/no-floating-promises` must stay on.

## Tests

- One test per acceptance criterion in `feature_list.json`.
- Test names describe the contract:
  `it("rejects empty project name")`, not `it("test 3")`.
- Use real temp dirs (`os.tmpdir()` + `fs.mkdtempSync`) for fs tests.

## Lint

- `eslint` clean (project config).
- `prettier --check .` clean.
- `tsc --noEmit` clean.
